<div id="review_878468145" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/878468145" />
    <a title="gaudeo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2428663-gaudeo"><img alt="gaudeo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1330366484p2/2428663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/878468145?book_show_action=true">Mar 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="gaudeo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="gaudeo" href="/user/show/2428663-gaudeo">gaudeo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer878468145" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13418684536175095522">This book is a story about a tenacious, resilient couple, former slaves, and their family-by-choice in the years after slavery, as they seek a safe place to settle and make homes of their own. Besides the grittiness, faith, and abiding hope of these people, what impresses this reader most is the resistance, resentment, and utter cruelty of a majority Southern whites during Reconstruction. I appreciate what this author achieved, even if I didn&apos;t appreciate her writing style, particularly the freq</span>
  <span id="freeText13418684536175095522" style="display:none">This book is a story about a tenacious, resilient couple, former slaves, and their family-by-choice in the years after slavery, as they seek a safe place to settle and make homes of their own. Besides the grittiness, faith, and abiding hope of these people, what impresses this reader most is the resistance, resentment, and utter cruelty of a majority Southern whites during Reconstruction. I appreciate what this author achieved, even if I didn't appreciate her writing style, particularly the frequent use of incomplete sentences and the unnecessary repetition of detail.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13418684536175095522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


