<div id="review_604635362" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/604635362" />
    <a title="Deborah Shaheed" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19954903-deborah-shaheed"><img alt="Deborah Shaheed" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/604635362?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah Shaheed" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah Shaheed" href="/user/show/19954903-deborah-shaheed">Deborah Shaheed</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer604635362" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17708255215947205444">This story chronicles the epic life of a family of newly freed slaves during the period of reconstructions. Cooper does a fantastic job of incorporating what many freed slaves had to deal with following their emancipation. It shows how the struggle for freedom did not end at emancipation and how a new, sinister ways to reenslaves blacks was a constant threat. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


