<div id="review_2927891470" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2927891470" />
    <a title="Sandy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9841783-sandy"><img alt="Sandy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1338237583p2/9841783.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2927891470?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandy" href="/user/show/9841783-sandy">Sandy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2927891470" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15011578160573168825">One of the best books I’ve read! And the best book about African Americans and their struggles I’ve found. <br/><br/>Set in the south during the last half of the 19th century, Wake of the Wind follows Lifee and Mor from slavery to freedom. Along their road of life they welcome others to become part of their “fambly.” I grew to love every character, felt their fear and joy, and was sad to come to the end of the book. A book about people of color that white people should read.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


